<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
  HC career-performance statistic. Drives the per-shift Performance bar in
  the expanded Career Panel and the promote/demote/fire thresholds in EA's
  CareerLevel logic.

  SHAPE
  -----
  Canonical Statistic TDESC (statistics/statistic.pyc INSTANCE_TUNABLES,
  cross-checked against Build/simdata/test/fixtures/tdescs/Statistic.tdesc.json
  and Constructor 5's Statistic.cs). Accepted tunables:

      initial_tuning           TunableTuple (_initial_value, _use_stat_value_on_init, _value_range)
      max_value_tuning         int
      min_value_tuning         int
      apply_value_to_object_cost, gallery_load_behavior, icon, min_lod_value,
      persisted_tuning, respect_lod_on_add, stat_asm_param, stat_name, telemetry

  `_use_stat_value_on_init` is set True per the TDESC requirement:
  "If unchecked, we error if any initial values are tuned as they imply
   that we want to use them."

  ISSUE #23 SAGA (this fix saved 4+ debug cycles, archived for posterity)
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------
  This resource was silently rejected by Sims 4 1.124.55's tuning loader
  across five separate fixes before we found the actual cause:

    1. `s="..."` 31-bit ID via smallInstanceIdFor — failed. We hypothesised
       the lot51-core "64-bit career truncation" bug applied to Statistic IDs.
    2. Hardcoded `s="99701"` then `s="99700"` — both failed. EA happens to
       have Max_RocketScience (Objective) at s=99700 and SC_Max_ItsNotBrainSurgery
       (Snippet) at s=99701; we suspected cross-type collisions.
    3. Hardcoded `s="109226"` (0x1AAAA, verified free across all 20518 EA
       CombinedTuning resources) — STILL failed. Ruled out collisions.
    4. Switched bare `<T n="initial_value">0</T>` to canonical
       `<U n="initial_tuning">...</U>` tuple — STILL failed. Ruled out shape.
    5. Empirical probe: shipped 3 control statistics (probeA same content,
       probeB minimal, probeC with "Historian" in name) alongside the broken
       one. All 3 probes registered; only the original kept failing. The one
       remaining difference: the original carried a 2898-byte XML comment
       block with em-dashes (U+2014). Stripping the comment fixed it.

  Resolution: Sims 4 1.124.55's tuning XML parser silently rejects a tuning
  resource whose source XML carries a multi-KB comment block, especially one
  containing Unicode characters. Failure mode: not registered into the type
  manager, no entry in lastException, no diagnostic anywhere — completely
  indistinguishable from an ID collision until you isolate the comment.

  Build-time mitigation: Build/s4tk-builder/build-package.mjs now strips all
  XML comments at load time, so source files can carry as much documentation
  as we want. THIS comment ships as zero bytes in the .package. The strip is
  the FIRST step after readFile, before any Pass-1 indexing — so the regex
  scans in resolve-names.mjs and the root-element parser never see comment
  content either.

  INSTANCE ID 109226 (0x1AAAA)
  ----------------------------
  Verified clear of EA's 20518-tuning index across all types. We could
  alternatively drop the literal s= and let smallInstanceIdFor compute a
  31-bit hash, but the hand-picked value keeps cross-references stable
  if we ever need to debug them in lastException output.

  RANGE -100..+100
  ----------------
  Matches every EA career performance stat. Critical for the CareerLevel
  scoring tunables (promote=100, demote=-80, fired=-95, warning=-50,
  base_performance=8 per shift, +5 per goal, -35 missed work) to land at
  sensible values rather than saturating immediately.
-->
<I c="Statistic" i="statistic" m="statistics.statistic" n="HC_PerformanceStat_Historian" s="109226">
  <U n="initial_tuning">
    <T n="_initial_value">0</T>
    <T n="_use_stat_value_on_init">True</T>
  </U>
  <T n="max_value_tuning">100</T>
  <T n="min_value_tuning">-100</T>
</I>
